{{Jainism}}
'''Acharya Bhutabali''' ({{circa|66|90 CE}}) was a [[Digambara monk]]. He along with Acharya [[Pushpadanta (Jain monk)|Pushpadanta]] composed the most sacred Jain text,'' [[Satkhandagama]].''

==Life==
Bhutabali led a group of monks to spread [[Jainism]] in [[Madurai]].<ref>{{citation |title=Jainism - Its relevance to psychiatric practice; with special reference to the practice of Sallekhana |pmc=5270277 }}</ref>

==Legacy==
''Shrut Panchami'' (scripture fifth) is celebrated by [[Jainism|Jains]] in may every year commemorating [[Pushpadanta (Jain monk)|Pushpadanta]] and Bhutabali.{{sfn|Dundas|2002|p=65}}

